(116, 1, '2018-04-19 01:49:22', '2018-04-19 01:49:22', '<p>Recently heard about Heap which seems pretty cool, but I’m not sure if it would really be valuable, or simply another tool that I need to check. We are not at the point of using HubSpot/Marketo yet so Heap’s free plan could be a useful stopgap tool.</p>\n<p>Do you use Heap? If so, what do you think?</p>\n<p>If not, what analytics tool do you use and what are the pros/cons?</p>\n', 'What are your thoughts on Google Analytics vs other analytics platforms?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-are-your-thoughts-on-google-analytics-vs-other-analytics-platforms', '', '', '2020-04-14 17:19:36', '2020-04-14 17:19:36', '', 0, 'https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/questions/what-are-your-thoughts-on-google-analytics-vs-other-analytics-platforms/', 0, 'question', '', 0),
(117, 1, '2018-04-19 01:59:21', '2018-04-19 01:59:21', '<p>Anyone else seeing dramatic ranking shakeups lately? Thankfully, this client is the blue line, but that’s a serious drop and recovery.</p>\n<p>We don’t operate at all in the black hat world, so our links and content should be in good shape. Anyone else seeing this kind of traffic dance lately?</p>\n', 'Google Analytics reads like a seismic chart lately', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'google-analytics-reads-like-a-seismic-chart-lately', '', '', '2020-04-14 17:17:00', '2020-04-14 17:17:00', '', 0, 'https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/questions/google-analytics-reads-like-a-seismic-chart-lately/', 0, 'question', '', 2),
(118, 1, '2018-04-19 02:00:31', '2018-04-19 02:00:31', 'In my local language (Bahasa Indonesia) there are no verb-2 or past tense form as time tracker. So, I often forget to use the past form of verb when speaking english.\n\nI saw him last night (correct)\n\nI see him last night (incorrect)\n\nBut i think both has the same meaning and are understandable,\n\nIsn’t it?', 'Is this statement, “i see him last night” can be understood as “I saw him last night”?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'is-this-statement-i-see-him-last-night-can-be-understood-as-i-saw-him-last-night', '', '', '2020-04-14 17:16:50', '2020-04-14 17:16:50', '', 0, 'https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/questions/is-this-statement-i-see-him-last-night-can-be-understood-as-i-saw-him-last-night/', 0, 'question', '', 4),
(119, 1, '2018-04-19 02:02:32', '2018-04-19 02:02:32', '<p>(Why I darest say, they darest not get offended when they so indeed have examples that violate their own use and nomenclature!) IE: pudding as a specific dessert, puddings as a general term for desserts. Calling something a Yorkshire pudding that is not a pudding and not a dessert.</p>\n', 'Why are the British confused about us calling bread rolls “biscuits” when they call bread rolls “puddings”?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'why-are-the-british-confused-about-us-calling-bread-rolls-biscuits-when-they-call-bread-rolls-puddings', '', '', '2020-04-14 17:16:43', '2020-04-14 17:16:43', '', 0, 'https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/questions/why-are-the-british-confused-about-us-calling-bread-rolls-biscuits-when-they-call-bread-rolls-puddings/', 0, 'question', '', 5),
(120, 1, '2018-04-19 02:02:52', '2018-04-19 02:02:52', '<p>I’m a 19-year-old student from Malaysia. I’ve been introduced to the language at a very young age and I’m capable of conducting any type of conversation. However, some of my English-speaking friends on the internet didn’t take too long to figure I’m not a native speaker. Why is that?</p>\n', 'How do native speakers tell I’m foreign based on my English alone?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-do-native-speakers-tell-im-foreign-based-on-my-english-alone', '', '', '2020-04-14 17:16:33', '2020-04-14 17:16:33', '', 0, 'https://2code.info/demo/themes/Discy/Main/questions/how-do-native-speakers-tell-im-foreign-based-on-my-english-alone/', 0, 'question', '', 3),
